inn1.comm: runs first up, as Sreesanth splays it on the pads and Gilchrist tucks it into the gap at square leg for a couple, to some cheer from the crowd
back of a length this time but still on leg, Gilchrist cant beat midwicket
goes for a booming extra-cover drive, to an inviting one outside off stump, but fails to connect by some margin
gets some bat on that one, not timed to perfection but its into the gap at point and the ball runs away, remember the square boundaries are short in Adelaide
tidier delivery, back of a length and going across Gilchrist, who leaves
good delivery, hits a length and comes in and Gilchrist defends it back
hits a good length outside off and Hayden nearly inside-edges back onto his boot as he defends with an angled bat
good delivery, seaming across Hayden and getting some good lift too at 140ks and Hayden is beaten as he drives, one-handed
troubles him again with the angle, the ball going across him at pace and height and Hayden takes a hand off the bat as he initially goes fishing
this one's on the pads and Hayden flicks it to midwicket
goes across him again and he leaves this one go, comfortably
beaten from the crease as he plays at it, then takes a hand off the bat, to a ball shaping across him off a good length ... this is good bowling from the youngster
back of a length outside off and he pushes it to point, watchfully
good shot, an on-the-rise drive between two men at point, wasn't an overpitched delivery but Gilchrist made the room himself
good delivery, getting sharp lift off a very nice seam position, Gilchrist pokes and misses as the ball leaves him
this time he covers his off stump and leaves one on a good length
gets forward and drives on the up again, but straight to cover-point
smashed, as Gilchrist goes aerial past the man at short cover, just freed the arms and teed off very, very hard
thats on the pads and Hayden's away, tucking to Harbhajan at midwicket
good length outside off stump and he leaves it alone
back of a length, good angle across Hayden, and he leaves it be
pitches outside leg and sits up, Hayden falls over in his attempted flick and Ishant does the fielding
goes chasing one and gets beaten, by that same lovely angle and bounce
just strives for too much and bowls it very wide of off stump
back of a length on leg stump, seams away and he's squared up, the ball rolls to cover
a loosener outside off, short and rising, Gilchrist chases it and the ball goes just over backward point and out to third man
better stuff, back of a length outside off and its poked to backward point
pitches outside off and straightens, Hayden gets across and shoulders arms
now where did that come from? Uff! Hayden just walks down the track and flays that with brute force rows back over deep midwicket
back of a length on off stump, this time he gets in line and defends
decent line, no room to work with and Hayden defends to cover
gets some lift from outside leg stump, the ball comes into Gilchrist's ribs and he defends it back to the bowler
good short one again, but he's overstepped, Gilchrist defends to point and then walks off towards leg to figure out what to do with the free hit
doesn't do much in the and, not giving himself any room and digs out a well-directed delivery in the blockhole back to Ishant's left side
first strike to India! Gilchrist doesn't move in his crease, just defending one that nips back in off a length and inside-edges back onto his stumps
good pace and bounce, rising outside off stump and Ponting leaves
thats too straight and Ponting works it towards square leg for one
good end to the over, forcing Hayden to defend to point
back of a length just outside off and Ponting defends to point
tidy delivery again, with good lift, and Ponting drops it at his feet
much fuller, 138ks, comes back in and Ponting gets an inside-edge
bang, thats four! Wasn't that short but Ponting pulls from outside off stump and smack through midwicket
whats that now? Ponting shapes to sweep, sort of standing up, swinging across the line and copping the ball in the midriff ... Munaf appeals but that cannot be out
slightly more orthodox defence, as he gets across and plays to midwicket
straighter one, get forward and pushes to mid-on, who's napping
gets forward and pushes at one, on the up, picking the gap at point
good length ball, Ponting gets onto the front foot and drives to cover
attempted bouncer goes down leg stump, and a wide called
short of a length, nips back in and Hayden has to defend it back
seams across from leg stump and Hayden pushes to the point fielder
sharp bounce into Hayden's ribs and he manages to tuck it out safely
gets him back in his crease, defending along the ground wide of gully
walks across his stumps and turns a straighter one to square leg
thats back of a length outside off stump and Hayden shoulders arms
gets forward and has to adjust his shot as the ball sits up, pushes to point
gets across his stump to nudge a shorter delivery to midwicket, good running
again he looks to get across but ends up defending one on leg to midwicket
digs in a short one to Hayden, who turns it away in the air to short fine leg
this one's fuller and Ponting drives expansively, getting an inside-edge to leg
back of a length and seaming across Hayden, who taps it back to Ishant
gets across to off stump, driving a length delivery to the man at cover
shorter one gets him on the back foot, cramping him into a defensive shot
good ball, good leave, as Hayden shoulders arms to one shaping across
and his poor form continues to haunt him! A short one bounces on him more than anticipated and he shapes to drive off the back foot, but the ball goes straight to Rohit at point
back of a length on the stumps and he gets in line to defend it back
hits a good length and he gets back to tap it back to Munaf again
good lift and carry outside off stump, Clarke opts to leaves this one be
marginally fuller length and he comes forward, driving to cover
pitches and straightens, Clarke pushes and gets a thick edge through gully
shortish one outside off, Hayden rides the bounce and plays to point
gets forward and drives a length ball, on the up, to the man at cover
edged and gone! Pathan strikes quickly, defeating Hayden with extra bounce as he tries to cut one too close to the body, and the edge is snapped up by Dhoni
he's off the mark immediately, tucking one off the pads to square leg
pitches back of a length and forces Clarke to defend to midwicket
a touch too straight and Clarke tucks it off the hips to square leg for one
short of a good length on the stumps and he opens the face, playing to point
tidy stuff, 135ks, good lift off the track as Clarke gets back and defends
134ks, a bit fuller and he gets an inside-edge to leg after defending
pitches on a good length and gets a nervy Clarke defending to cover
134ks, hits a length and goes away and Clarke judges well, opting to shoulder arms even though his front foot wasn't to the pitch
thats a maiden as Munaf again hits a length and Clarke defends to the fielder
good length on off stump, Symonds stands his ground and defends to cover
extra bounce gets Symonds leaving the ball just in time, and Dhoni takes
pushes this one across him and he leaves it be off the front foot
gets this one to nip back in and Symonds, squared up, runs it to point
good single, Symonds defending another one that comes back in, with soft hands to point, and Clarke pushes for the run
a touch too short and Clarke gets onto the back foot, driving to extra cover
back of a length outside off, chopped with an angled bat towards gully
much fuller, Clarke drives well but Uthappa, at short cover, dives to stop it
this one's shorter and seaming away, Clarke chases with absolutely no movement of the feet and gets beaten
137ks, a touch too straight and Clarke drives to mid-on, running hard
138ks, comes back in off a length but Symonds opts to leave it be
comes in again from off and he presents a full face back to the bowler
139ks, good bounce outside off stump, Clarke leaves it be
comes forward to a fuller one and drives to cover, where Gambhir dives to his right and takes some pace off the shot with one hand and Yuvraj does the cleaning up at mid-off
good carry from a shorter one, it comes in to Symonds, who leaves
gets forward and pushes one to cover, who stops it

another one bites the dust! Symonds tries to steer one just too close to the body, as it comes back in at extra height, and the ball goes nowhere but into gully's hands ... a superb decision to bring Ishant back for the first over of the final Powerplay
sits up again, he gets forward and defends to point, watchfully
gets up and plays one around the corner, for a single, Dhoni fields
a touch too full and Hussey steers it wide of backward point for one
gets forward and leaves a good-length delivery wide of off stump
this time he decides to push the ball to extra cover, but cant beat the man
sees the shorter length and drives on the up, but Uthappa dives at cover and saves certain runs, good stop there
flashes hard at this one, off the back foot, and finds the gap at cover-point
pitches on a good length and Hussey square-drives to Gambhir at point
short of a length, good lift off the surface and Clarke leaves it be
this one moves in off a short length but Clarke can afford to leave again
nagging, outside-the-off channel and Clarke has to leave it once more
thats marginally full and Clarke drives to Pathan at mid-off, who commits an absolute blunder - I'm talking needless dive and nice gap through the hands - to allow the batsman a four down the ground
the response is a short-of-a-length ball and Clarke goes back to leaving
gets onto the front foot and runs one wide of Gambhir at backward point
hits a length and straightens, Clarke gets forward and shoulders arms
138ks, sharp one sits up and surprises Clarke, who does well to ride the bounce and drop the ball in front of midwicket for a sharp single
tight line, getting Hussey back in the crease and defending it back
thats a good length on off stump and he defends watchfully to cover
143ks, good length outside off and he gets bat and pad together
hint of movement through the air, full length, Hussey blocks it out to point
good length on middle and off, patiently pushed back to Pathan
this one nips back and Clarke gets an inside-edge to cover as he drives
seams across Clarke, pretty wide too, and he watches it through to Dhoni
touch too straight, Clarke drives off the pads, but again cant beat midwicket
bouncer this time over the stumps, forcing Clarke to duck under it
strays onto leg stump and Clarke tucks it away for a single to end the over
good length outside off stump, comes onto the front foot and pushes to point
bowls a good length just outside off and Hussey patiently defends to cover
back of a length this time and he leaves it be, pretty close to the body, too
too wide and he jams bat down on it, piercing the gap at point for a triple
walks across the stumps and flicks a full one to a diving midwicket fielder
this one's driven straight through Sreesanth's legs but mid-off fields
hits a good length outside off stump and Hussey shoulders arms
back of a length, with some good carry, as Hussey again leaves alone
back of a length, Hussey leaves, Dhoni collects and flings it to cover
slower one, a touch fuller and wider but again Hussey wants to leave it be
pitches down leg, Hussey shuffles across and dabs it to square leg, calling immediately for the sharp single ... Pathan raises his arms in frustration
now thats timed well, as Clarke pounces on the short one and slaps it nicely through the covers for four ... this time Pathan puts hands to hips and walks off
133ks, nips in off a good length and Hussey pushes into the covers
back of a length outside off and Clarke gets forward, only to leave it be
too full down leg stump and he clips off the boot to backward square leg
full outside off, Hussey advances and drives to Raina, the sub, at cover
hits a fullish length and nips in, Hussey defends comfortably to point
bowls a good length and Hussey drives to cover, but straight to Raina
thats a wide, just going across a bit too much
uses his feet and drives a good-length ball to extra cover, timed but not placed
gets across to a length ball and defends it watchfully
gets some extra width and punches off the back foot out to cover sweeper

edged and taken! Pathan gets his second, striving for swing and inviting Hussey into a drive outside off stump, he succeeds in getting movement in the air and off the pitch and the thin edge is gleefully accepted by Dhoni
thats a gift, well outside leg stump and Hopes clips superbly down to fine leg
thats a length on off stump, he gets forward and drives to mid-off
back of a length outside off and its driven towards backward point
a touch short again and he drives off the back foot, but to the fielders
straighter one, Clarke works it across the line, uppishly, to midwicket
full on off stump, wristily flicked to the man at midwicket, and he gets one now
flashes at one off the back foot, steering just wide of backward point
gets on top of a length delivery and drives hard to extra cover, but no run
good, positive shot to a full delivery on off stump, Hopes driving straight back past Pathan's outstretched left and mid-off is sloppy, so they run hard and get three
just short of a length outside off stump and Clarke punches in the air, past a diving short cover, and Ishant covers up from mid-off
thats a needless one, short over leg stump and called wide for height
pitches well outside leg stump, Hopes tucks if out to deep backward square
slower ball, full on off stump, flicked past square leg for a well-run two
back of a length but a touch wide and Clarke pushes into the covers for one
thats too short and wide and Hopes gets over it, cutting wide of point
thats a ripper, kicking off sharply from off stump and trapping Hopes deep in the crease, deflection off the pads and it runs fine
tossed up on leg stump and Clarke nudges it towards square leg
flat one, gets a firm stride in and works it around the corner for one
tossed up on off stump, he makes room and cuts to backward point
flatter one, spins down leg stump and Clarke tucks it to square leg
full and flat and Clarke smashes it through a diving extra cover for four, lovely shot to end the over

short of a length on off stump, Hopes gets forward, then back, and pushes to point, calls for the run and there's a chance for a run out but Munaf fails to get back to the stumps to collect ... had he been there, it would've been dicy
slower ball, on a good length and Clarke defends watchfully to cover
good length outside off and he drives to short cover this time
gets over a short one and punches off the back foot, but straight to cover
shorter one on off, he opens the face and guides it into the gap at point
short, wide and cut hard in the air wide of backward point for four
spins down leg stump, Dhoni collects and thats wide
thats a shot! Clarke uses his feet and makes room for himself, then drives hard and inside-out over extra cover for a one-bounce four
flat one down leg stump, he shuffles and works it to midwicket
shuffles across to off, Harbhajan fires it flat, Hopes tucks to square leg
tosses it up outside off, Hopes gets across and dabs it wide of point
gives it some air on middle and off, he gets well forward and smothers it
fractionally short on leg stump and he pulls out to deep square leg
flat on leg stump, he shuffles and tucks it into the gap at midwicket for one
tossed up on off stump and its driven back to his right side
touch flatter and he drives it hard to Uthappa at short extra cover
slower one, tossed up outside off stump and Hopes defends
flat outside off stump, Hopes drives towards mid-off and sets off for one
looped up outside off stump, Clarke defends watchfully to end the over
tossed up, drifts into middle and leg, Hopes works it off the pads to leg

thats lovely teamwork! Harbhajan tosses up the doosra, Hopes doesn't pick it all as he advances out of his crease, the ball goes on past his bat and Dhoni completes an easy stumping .. and Australia have slipped even further into a hole
tossed up on leg stump, he firmly gets bat and pad together in defence
tosses it up outside leg, raps Hogg on on the flap of the knee roll
flatter one outside off stump, Hogg uses his feet and drives to deep cover
full and flat down leg stump and Clarke clips out to deep midwicket
tossed up outside off, Clarke waits for it to spin and then pushes to point
tossed up on off stump, driven with an inside-edge to midwicket
tossed up wider, he gets back and drives into the covers
touch too wide and Clarke makes room, cutting past point for two
flatter one on off stump, Clarke shuffles and works it across the line
tossed up on a length and Hogg pushes tentatively to the cover fielder
flat on middle and off, spins in and Clarke nudges to midwicket for one
shorter one, spins wide and Hogg chases, but cant beat the man at slip
81ks, pushed across him wider and he leaves this one be
quicker and flatter outside off stump, he drives and inside-edges
gives it some flight outside off and Hogg drives to cover this time
too short and Hogg cuts through the gap at point for a single to keep strike
tossed up on off stump, he shuffles across and drives to midwicket
holds back the length a touch and Hogg plays it back towards Yuvraj
flat one on off stump, he drives across the line for a quick single
looped up outside off stump, Clarke gets forward and defends
thats a quicker one, short outside off and Clarke misses out on the cut
quick and flat on the stump, Clarke gets in line and turns it past midwicket
flat across off stump, pushed to point and he gets sent back by Clarke
flat on off stump, Hogg makes room to leg and ends up pushing it back
low full toss outside off stump is slashed wide of backward point for one
spins down middle stump and pins him back in his crease, defending
topspinner, goes on and Clarke picks it, getting back and pushing to point
walks across his stumps and pats a flatter one to midwicket
touch too short outside off stump and Hogg cuts it wide of backward point
heavy heave across the line to bring up a hard-earned fifty, as Clarke gets down and swipes a flat one over midwicket
short and wide, he rocks back and punches into the covers
slower one, still flat outside off stump, Hogg drives it to point for one
too short again, Clarke gets onto the back foot and drives wide of point
again just too short and Hogg pounces on it, flaying it through a diving gully and the ball just manages to trickle over the third man ropes
touch too short, Clarke sees it and backs away, cutting into the covers
tossed up on middle and leg, good bounce, Hogg pats it back to the bowler
tossed up outside off and Hogg patiently defends to cover
flat on leg stump, Hogg works it into the gap for a single
slower one, holds back the length and Clarke checks the shot to cover
short and wide, he makes room and carves wide of gully and Munaf is, as always, sluggish to get to the ball at third man and they run three
he oversteps, bowls it wide and Clarke pushes into the covers and we have another free hit coming up
thats how you deal with them! Clarke makes room and slashes over extra cover and right into the gap ... are we onto something big from Clarke?
slower and straighter, he shuffles and drives past midwicket this time
drives one off a good length into the gap at cover and point, well hit
gets tall and drives a length delivery into the covers, but the fielder is sharp
too straight and Clarke raises the 150 with a clip to square leg
full and straight again, he gets back and pushes it to Ishant's right
flat outside off stump, Clarke gets back and drives to Harbhajan
too full and flat down leg stump and he flicks into midwicket
works a tossed up delivery off the pads into the gap at square leg
tosses it up down leg stump, Clarke nudges to square leg
touch shorter, spins wide and Uthappa dives at slip to save runs
but that one's just wide of Uthappa, steered intelligently by Hogg for one
short and wide but Hogg cannot beat point with his lusty cut shot
mistimes his drive outside off stump, the ball stopping on him
chases a short one from the crease and slashes over gully for one
slower ball, on a length, but Clarke still pushes a single towards point
gets to the pitch and drives into the covers this time, but no chance of a run
good length outside off, Hogg drives again but can't beat extra cover
flat on off stump, Clarke gets in line and defends it back
touch fuller and he uses his feet, on-driving down the ground for one
too short outside off, allowing Hogg room to cut into the covers
sees the length and moves to leg, steering the ball into the covers
flatter one on the stumps, Hogg drives and Harbhajan fields to his left
flat outside off stump, he makes room and cuts past point for one
short and wide, Hogg runs it wide of gully and Pathan collects at third man, firing in a throw but Munaf again is nowhere near the stumps, thats very shoddy
back of a length again he steers it towards backward point for one
good length outside off, Clarke gets right over it and pushes to extra cover
slower one, touch fuller, Hogg mistimes his attempted dab to Dhoni
beats him this time as Hogg drives with no footwork, the ball seaming away
too wide and Hogg drives into the gap between cover and point for one
slow ball, almost a low full toss, clipped straight to midwicket
good swing, nipping back in sharply and cramping Hogg for room, he manages to bring bat down in time and tucks it to midwicket again
good length outside off stump and Hogg drives nicely to mid-off, a direct hit comes in but the batsmen have crossed safely
goes for a big shot after walking across his stumps, but finds midwicket
slants this one across Clarke, who flashes it to Munaf at third man
half-volley outside off stump but Hogg drives it straight to Gambhir at cover
sees some width and flashes hard, edging wide of where first slip would be, Harbhajan stops it near the third man ropes
full on middle and off, 130ks, driven to midwicket for one
back of a length on off and he makes room and edges wide of gully
runs a length delivery from off stump down to third man, expertly
just too full and Hogg drives superbly past Munaf at mid-off for four
drives one from off stump to cover and sprints off for one, well run
pitches on a length and Hogg pushes into the covers for a quick single
uses his feet and drives in the air down to long-off, just a single though
bit too full and wide and Hogg carves past backward point for one
he really reaches out to slap that wide one past cover and point
strays down leg stump and Hogg turns it out to deep backward square
bowls it short and Clarke pulls from outside off stump out to the sweeper

comes out, Harbhajan sees him coming and fires it full and flat, Hogg inside-edges back past leg stump and Clarke wants the single, Dhoni makes good ground and there really was no run there, so Hogg has to sacrifice his wicket for his senior partner as Harbhajan accepts the throw and does the needful
full and flat and Clarke kneels down and swats to deep midwicket
flat on off stump, Johnson pushes forward to the man at cover for one
full down leg stump, Clarke heaves it to midwicket and sets off but a poor throw reprieves him
low full toss outside off stump and Johnson drives it back to Harbhajan
tight delivery, full outside off stump and Johnson makes a mess of it
gone! Clarke goes pulling a slower delivery, short though it was, straight down the throat of a well-positioned Ishant at deep midwicket
almost another run out, as Bracken pushes one to gully, Johnson sets off but has to retract his paces and dive back inside
beaten, as Pathan uses a good angle to work it across Bracken
swing and a miss! Bracken tries to go downtown but cannot connect
and thats another, as Pathan works that channel to suck Bracken into a loose drive outside off stump, good outswinger, and Dhoni dives to his right to hold the thick edge
he drives loosely and misses, so Pathan will have to stay at four for now
tossed up, he drives in the air but in bounces in front of cover
well bowled, very full and flat and Johnson drives it back to the bowler
low full toss, Johnson uses his feet and drives down to long-on
gives it some air outside off and Clark runs it past Dhoni to third man
full and pretty wide, Johnson heaves at it and edges into the ground at gully
full and flat on the stumps and Clark clips it to midwicket for one
too full and wide as he strives for swing and Clark square-drives for two
walks across to off before the ball is bowled and pushes to point
full and straight, change of pace too, and Johnson drives to long-on
bowls a length outside off, Clark gets across and dabs it past gully
full on the stumps, swings in and Johnson clips out to deep square leg
and he almost gets five, slipping in a slower one that Johnson inside-edges back onto his back leg before he scampers a single
full on the stumps and its heaved out to deep midwicket, raising the 200
tries to make room and then swings at a length ball just over off stump, but cannot make any contact ... a crucial dot ball
backs away to leg stump, Ishant bowls it slow and wide, then Clark has to adjust and reach out, slapping it in the air down to third man
now Johnson gives him the charge so he holds back the length to beat him
full and straight outside off stump, Johnson gets the toe end of the bat on it and scampers a single into the covers
full on the stumps and Clark drives into the covers for one

inn2.comm: full and swinging already and Gambhir plays a punchy shot to point
back of a length outside off stump and Gambhir shoulders arms
sees some width and square-drives on the rise but can't beat point
makes some room for himself, walking down the track to drive through extra cover, its not timed to perfection but he gets two
134ks, just back of a good length and Gambhir pokes to point
some width there and Gambhir cracks a flashy drive through backward point and out to the fielder running around from third man
bit of swing first up and Tendulkar eases the ball to point
that swings away sharply off a length, across the breeze, and its left alone
firm push into the covers, to a fullish one, but can't beat the fielders
gets his foot forward and then shoulders arms, as the ball carries on
thats quicker, 139ks and lifting outside off, for Tendulkar to leave
sharp one zips in from leg stump to catch him high on the flap as he hops
comes dancing down but can't put a full one away past mid-on
sharper line, coming back in at 137ks and Gambhir defends
short and wide and slashed over where third slip would have been, it lands safely and disturbs some seagulls chilling at third man
nips back into him off a length but he rolls the wrists, working to square leg
thats about 134ks and swinging, Tendulkar gently defends it back
holds back the length and shapes it across Tendulkar, who is beaten
strays outside leg stump and Gambhir helps it on its way to fine leg, where the fielder was very square, and again he scatters seagulls down there
this one's angled wide of off stump and Gambhir can't get to it
pitches outside leg stump and swings away sharply, wide called
again outside leg stump, this time Gambhir nudges to midwicket for one
tucks him up on leg stump and he works it straight to midwicket
a touch fuller, with a hint of swing, and this time he works it square leg
and he's off the mark, cutting a short one to the right of backward point
edged and it goes smack between first slip and wicketkeeper, would you believe! Bracken sucked Tendulkar into a tame shot, a perfect edge, but neither Hayden not Gilchrist moved!
back of a length outside off and he leaves this one be
again he causes him trouble with that nagging length, forcing him to push down the wrong line and miss it all ends up
rapped on the pads and he's gone! Tendulkar, already given a work over by Bracken, shapes to flick a full one leg stump but misses, they all appeal and the verdict is given in Bracken's favour
left alone outside off
outside off and moving away, lunging to the ball, thick outside edge trickles to third man for a single
short of a length, probing outside off and going away from the left-hander, wafts and misses, loose shot there
full and swinging into the left-hander, 130kph, dug out and deflects onto his legs
slightly short, outside off, moving away, shoulders arms this time
short again, outside off and Pathan jabs it towards point for a single, well in the gap that time
on the pads this time, Gambhir cramped for room, can't get it away, stifled appeal for lbw but that was going down leg
full and outside off, swinging a shade in, thick inside edge onto the leg side, Gambhir lets out a grunt, he knew that was in the slot for a cover-drive
driven confidently to cover
full and into middle stump, 136.5kph, nudged away to the leg side

short of a length, Gambhir tries to jab it to the off side but can only manage a thick inside edge down to third man, that was played away from the body and could have easily gone onto the stumps, vacant fine-leg region, though, and they get three
punched off the back foot, they think of a single but Symonds pulls off a fine save at cover
short of a length, pushed down the ground to mid-off
short of a length and outside off, another loose flash outside off and Pathan can't make contact again
back of a length and moving too much outside off, wide is the call
hits a tighter length and Gambhir defends towards cover
dances down and looks to go over mid-on but  gets a thick edge wide of gully
goes for a booming drive outside off stump, beaten by a mile
lovely seam, 136.6ks, sits up sharply and Pathan misses again
third ball in a row Pathan plays and misses, reaching out too wide
this time he gets forward and shoulders arms, wisely
comes back in off a length and Gambhir confidently leaves it be
nips in again, this time from off stump, and Gambhir pokes to point
touch too short but not enough to cut freely and he chops to point
short of a length again, very tidy, and Gambhir cannot beat gully this time
this time he manages to dab it wide of gully and gets a single
touch too short and Pathan clubs it into the ground with loads of bottom hand
tries to create room and cuts, but misses the shorter ball outside off
hits the seam and goes away, Gambhir judges it and shoulders arms
sits up outside off stump and he tries to uppercut, but again misses out
good single, simply dabbed into the covers and well called for
fraction short and wide and Pathan cracks it through point for four
now he goes for a pull shot but misses as the ball gains on him rapidly
short and wide, cracked hard but to Clarke at backward point
short of a length again, he gets across and runs it towards gully
good length, seam up, Pathan defends with an inside-edge to midwicket
yorker down leg stump, thuds into Pathan's boot as he tries to flick, there's no swing on that ball, umpire Parker doesn't think it would have hit leg stump
gets over a good-length ball and drives into the covers for a quick single
gets some width and gives it the kitchen sink, slashing over backward point and out to the sweeper, Hopes, who slides and cuts them to two
there's a shot! Pathan crunches it on the up, coming forward, through point
driven on the up again, but straight to the man at cover
slides down leg stump, Gilchrist dives but fumbles and wide is called
slower one, 123ks, played with soft hands wide of gully for one
makes some room and drives a fuller one straight to Symonds at cover
slides down leg stump, Pathan turns it into the gap at midwicket
greets the half-volley with an on-the-up steer through point, for a couple
hits a good length and its driven back to the left of Johnson, who fields
sits up off a wider angle and Pathan cuts to the man at point
a touch fuller and Pathan drives nicely into the covers, Hogg dives at mid-off and saves runs with a good stop
marginally short and he brings the bat down hard, cutting to an athletic Clarke at point
slower ball outside off stump, 132ks, stops on him and he drags the offcutter across the line towards midwicket, early into the shot
that'll be the 50, as Pathan works one off the pads to the gap behind square
back of a length on the stumps, he gets across and plays it back
short one on the stumps and he plays a pull, not perfect at all, but its up and into the gap at deep midwicket
this one slants across him and he dabs, with soft hands, past gully
lovely seam position there, sitting up and beating his bat as he drives
false shot gets Hopes a wicket! Pathan pokes at one that pitches on leg stump and goes across him, and Hayden takes a good low catch at gully
short of a length, 138ks, and he defends loosely outside off stump
hits a good length, he pushes it to extra cover, where there's a misfield, and Rohit calls for the second against Hogg's throw
slower ball outside off stump, stops on him and he drives loosely to mid-on
back of a length and seaming in, Gambhir opens the face and runs it fine
well played, rising to counter the bounce and then steering it through a diving Clarke at backward point, for a single
sharp catch, Ponting! India lose a third as Gambhir rises and slashes a short and wide one straight to the captain, at backward point
fullish delivery on off stump and he gets in line, driving back to the bowler

and another one bites the dust! Hopes gets a second in quick time as Rohit plays the poorest of leaden-footed drives to one shaping away from the body and edges a regulation take to Gilchrist, cuing celebrations around the ground
good length outside off stump and Dhoni pushes it straight to cover
back of a length outside off stump, he has a look and leaves it alone
straightens off a short length and Dhoni compactly defends to cover
good bouncer, 138.7ks and that zips past Dhoni's shoulder, forcing him up in the air, aggression from Hopes, at good pace!
another short one gets Dhoni hopping and leaving outside off stump
back of a length on off stump, pushed to Symonds at point this time
fuller outside off stump, he tentatively pushes forward to cover
back of a length outside off stump, he gets across and shoulders arms
well bowled, a 142k-yorker and he jams bat down in time
full toss on the pads and he whips that out to deep backward square
pitches on leg and straightens, Dhoni tucks it out to deep fine leg and hustles for the second, really pushing Yuvraj on that occasion
tidy line, about leg stump and rising, and Yuvraj pushes it back to Hopes
nips across him this time and he gets right in line, defending it back
back of a good length, he gets across to off stump and pushes to cover
slower ball, full outside off stump and he plonks it to the man at point
shapes this one across Yuvraj, who has a look-see and decides to leave
fraction short and he drives off the back foot to Symonds at cover
inches forward and drives a good-length delivery into the covers
reaches out and plays a wristy cover-drive through point for a single
fuller one outside off, he opens the face and steers to Hussey at cover
thats a perfect bouncer, very fast, and sucking Yuvraj into the air but he survives as the thick outside-edge flies in the gap between Gilchrist and second slip
full on the pads and he clips it down to fine leg for a single
drives a wide half-volley through the covers and out to Symonds in the deep
gets tall and drives off the back foot to the man at cover
thats a fuller length and Yuvraj watchfully defends to Clarke at point
beaten! Yuvraj's feet don't move as he flirts outside off stump, poor shot
firm back-foot punch but straight to Hussey in the covers
gets right across to off and drives off the back foot, down to mid-off
full one as Hopes looks for swing, square-driven off the front foot to point
142ks, back of a length outside off and Dhoni pokes it to point
reaches out and drives a full one to Hopes, doing duty at extra cover
walks across the crease and works the ball into the onside, very smartly, and Gilchrist has to run all the way down to fine leg to field
thats a jaffa, 145ks and short, getting Yuvraj jumping up in the air but crucially he watched the ball and dropped the hands as he left it be

full on off stump, Yuvraj drives back hard and the ball hits Dhoni's left hand, else that was screaming away to the long-on ropes ... Johnson has overstepped, so we have India's first free hit ... but first, some attention for Dhoni's left pinky finger
full on the pads and he flicks it through midwicket and the sweeper cannot get around in time to cut it off
full and wide outside off stump and Yuvraj laces the square-drive superbly, a shot that will give him plenty of confidence
looped up on off stump, spins in and Dhoni works it to midwicket
thats short but Dhoni mistimes his twirling punch into the covers
drifts outside leg stump and he tucks it straight to square leg
spins flatter, Yuvraj  gets across and picks the wrong 'un with the turn
flat on off stump, spins in and Dhoni works it across to square leg
uses his feet and drives a fuller one to mid-off, keeping hold of the strike
short and flat and Dhoni drills that past mid-off for a single
full and flat on middle and leg, flicked past midwicket out to Johnson
lobbed up wide off stump, Dhoni reaches out and works it to midwicket
flat outside off stump, Dhoni reaches for it and pushes in the air to cover
still full and wide and this time he drives to the right of the cover fielder
reaches for the width and square-drives just wide of Clarke at point
well he's smacked the pants off that one! Hogg serves up a rank long hop which Yuvraj pelts flat over mid-on for six
beaten in flight, as Hogg tosses it up outside off stump
flat outside off stump, he reaches for it and defends to cover
sees the width and carves the ball out to deep cover sweeper
flatter one, sits up outside off and he pushes to point for a quick single
flighted wide of the stumps and he square-drives to backward point
walks across his stumps and cheekily paddles around the corner, into the gap at short fine leg ... well played, but Symonds isn't happy
again he walks across and paddles one wide of Clark a square leg
tossed up on off stump, he gets across and flicks to midwicket
flat on middle and off, Dhoni gets back and drives to Symonds
full and flat outside off, driven back to Symonds, who misfields
flatter trajectory, touch short, Yuvraj stands up and drives to the fielder
bit too short and Dhoni flat-bats it to mid-off, Yuvraj bolts out of his crease but turns back hurriedly as Dhoni sends him back, Clark's throw misses his target
gives him the charge, going through extra cover, firmly struck shot that
slides down leg stump and Dhoni nudges it into the gap for a couple
goes for another flat-batted swipe but Hogg reacts quickly and fields
this one's got some air on it, so Dhoni reaches for it and drives past cover
good loop and dip on this one, drawing a false defence along the ground
short of a length and he dabs it wide of Clarke at backward point, who reacts a little late and misses the stumps as Yuvraj just grounds his bat
132ks, back of a length and Yuvraj drives it back off the back foot
a tad fuller in length and he drives handsomely into the covers
goes for a big drive again but the bat turns in his hands, so the ball rolls along the ground to the fielder at midwicket
shorter length and a bit wide, Yuvraj angles the bat but can't beat gully
seams back in off a length, he opens the face but can't beat Gilchrist
looped up on leg stump and he turns it away past square leg with ease
short and spinning away, Yuvraj steers it uppishly to gully where Hussey lobs in a throw to Hogg, who misfields and allows the single
flatter outside off stump, driven back to Hogg this time
chaos! Hogg serves it up full, Dhoni drives to Clark at mid-off, sets off, the fielder misses the stumps and gives up overthrows and Dhoni hustles Yuvraj, superb running
beaten again, he Hogg flights it and Yuvraj pushes down the wrong line
thats the breakthrough for Hogg! Yuvraj throws it all away, clubbing a long hop out to wide deep long-on, where Clark covers good ground and cups the catch near his ankles
good length on the stumps, he shuffles across and plays it back to Bracken
on target again and Uthappa defends into the covers, watchfully
a touch fuller this time, Uthappa inches forward and defends to cover
back of a length on leg stump, Uthappa tucks it back to Bracken
back of a length again, he gets up and taps it to the man at point
well-targeted full delivery and Uthappa can only play it back to Bracken
flighted up on middle and off, defended along the ground to point
touch too flat and Dhoni cuts past Ponting in the covers for one
flat on leg stump, paddled around the corner for a single
flights it up and beats him as he goes driving outside off stump
pitches on leg and spins down, catching Dhoni high on the knee roll
flatter one spins across him and he just leaves it be for Gilchrist
full on the stumps and Uthappa turns it out to deep midwicket

pushes at one and it runs away off the outside-edge to third man, they get two and Uthappa then presses for the third, Gilchrist goes a long way out to collect the throw from Hopes at third man and replays show Uthappa grounded his bat in time
back of a length and seaming away, Uthappa gets tall and leaves it be
gets over the bounce and taps it to Clarke at backward point
fuller on off stump, he uses his feet and clips it to midwicket
on the money, no room at all and Uthappa plays it back to Clark
flat on off stump and Dhoni digs it back to Hogg's left side
flat on leg stump and he works it into the gap at square leg for one
looped up on middle and off, Uthappa clips it wide of midwicket for one
thats a low full toss that Dhoni hammers to mid-on
flat one spins way and he makes a mess, pulling straight to midwicket
gets down and paddles one from leg stump, very hard, to Clark at fine leg
too straight and Uthappa walks across, turning the ball to square leg
slower ball on a length and he steers it to point, calling for the single
tight delivery, on a length and Uthappa just pats it back to Clark
good length, on off stump, and he plays it back to Clark again
slips down leg stump, Gilchrist reacts well and saves runs but he yelps out in pain, looks like the ball thudded into the end of the fingers
back of a length outside off stump and he gets up, pushing to point
moves across to off stump and dabs the ball into the covers
140ks, hits the money and Uthappa can just push it to point
that'll be wide, as Johnson pitches well outside leg stump
slower ball outside off and he steers it to Clarke at backward point
shuffles around in his crease and ends up playing it back to the bowler
again he walks across and chips it in the air just over midwicket's head
gets onto the front foot early and steers the ball to Clarke at point
tries to tuck a short one off the hips but the ball gets all tangled up, dropping at his feet as Rohit tries sneaking in a cheeky single
gets forward and pushes a full delivery through point, calling for two immediately and Uthappa and Rohit do so well too
back of a length and he steers it to Clarke at backward point

ah, a poor call! Impatiently driven into the covers, with too much bottom hand, Dhoni calls for the single but a diving, sliding Rohit is caught just short by a terrific direct hit from Hayden and Dhoni pays for that risky call
gets back to steer a short delivery through gully for another single
back of a length and Harbhajan gets up to push the ball to cover
short one outside off stump and he plays an awkward flick past square leg for one, but kept down along the ground
short one down leg stump, Harbhajan misses and a wide is called
firm stroke, a back-foot drive past Symonds at mid-off for three
short of a length outside off stump, 143ks, steered to point
presses forward and dabs this one wide of gully, to third man
that one's angled pretty wide of off stump and Harbhajan cant get there
tight delivery on off stump receives a tight back-foot defensive
undone by pace and bounce! Johnson springs in a short one that Harbhajan tamely pulls up into the air, Gilchrist takes an easy catch and then erupts in celebration
hits a length on off stump and Uthappa plays it right back to Hopes
stands his ground and defends it towards point, with no hurry
aggressive intent, advancing and connecting well, smacking Hopes over extra cover and the ball dribbles into the boundary
gets cheeky, paddling the ball from off stump and down to fine leg, where Johnson has plenty to do to run around and cut it off
sharp bouncer outside off stump, Sreesanth watches it go past
stands in his crease and patiently defends a short delivery
slower ball off an angle, just 123ks and it beats Uthappa
very quick bouncer outside off stump, the effort ball, Uthappa goes hooking and fails to make contact ... there's words shared and Uthappa walks down the track
saunters down the track and swings wildly, but misses all ends up
thats absolutely drilled back past the bowler, but a well-time slide on the ropes by Symonds and a quick release cuts off a boundary
gone! Uthappa makes room and tries to play a cute little dab, but the change of pace from Johnson does him in, and he gets a thin touch through to Gilchrist
genuine pace and bounce, 148.4ks, gets Ishant hopping
low full toss outside off stump, Sreesanth drives to cover for one
flighted up slow, Ishant plonks forward and takes the ball high on the knee roll, Gilchrist and Hogg appeal but umpire Parker reckons he was outside the line
fuller and flatter and Ishant flicks it to midwicket
stumped! Hogg proposes, Sreesanth accepts, dancing out and swiping across the line, he misses the wrong 'un and Gilchrist takes care of the rest
quicker one outside off stump, he gets forward and plays to cover
flatter one outside off stump and he misses the line completely
short, fast and rising and Ishant chases, missing by a country mile
straighter and fuller and he tentatively drives into the covers
full and wide, inviting the drive but Ishant leaves that one be
full on the pads and he clips just in front of Hussey at short fine leg
beaten by the shorter one, as he stands and wafts outside off stump
slower one slips out a full toss but he doesn't pick it, and misses
beaten in the flight as Hogg pushes it through quicker outside off stump
sweeps a flat one on leg stump, a hard throw comes back to Hogg's end
flatter one spins down and Munaf awkwardly plays it back to Hogg
quicker one, 98ks on leg stump, played back to Hogg
this one spins across him and he steers it to the man at gully
full and flat and Munaf makes room, driving the ball to cover
serves up a low full toss that he drives to cover, there was a second there but Munaf stands his ground

edged and well held! Bracken moves around the stumps and gets Munaf edging to Gilchrist, who initially moves to his left but adjusts to pluck a good one-handed catch to his right ... thats five dismissals for him today and he jumps about in celebration
